File: Deputy secretary-general Jessie Duarte said private businesses and individuals producing masks with ANC branding should not abuse the party's logo. JOHANNESBURG - ANC deputy secretary-general Jessie Duarte has appealed to people selling masks with the ANC logo to desist. WATCH: Masks can protect against COVID-19 The secretary-general said private businesses and individuals producing masks with ANC branding should not abuse the party's logo. "This flies in the face of the unity that is being forged in fighting against COVID-19," Duarte said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.